dcterms:description: High-resolution GPS collars track 26 individuals of a troop of olive baboons (Papio anubis) living in the wild in Mpala Research Centre, Kenya. The data consists of latitude-longitude location pairs for each individual at one observation per second.
dcterms:title: GPS tracks of a baboon troop

dcterms:description: Video-tracking of fish schools where 70 fish, including 10 trained individuals, were tracked to study information propagation over the visual fields of fish during 24 separate leadership events.
dcterms:title: Video-tracking of fish schools

dcterms:description: Daily closing price data for stocks listed in NASDAQ from January 2000 to January 2016, focusing on discovering different intervals of coordination and the leaders involved in these coordinated events.
dcterms:title: Stock market closing price data of the NASDAQ index
mls:task: Identifying leaders in stock market events
